description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifesaving, life-changing administration.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT), effective administration is key to developing stronger, more effective services. It’s one of the foundations that will help us become the best donation service in the world for blood, organs, tissues and stem cells. And we need dedicated administrators who can run the offices and departments that will get us there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role overview &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll provide the comprehensive administration and support that allows our Research and Development (R&amp;D) office to run smoothly and effectively. The role covers a broad range of administrative duties and you’ll play a key role in enabling the office to produce exceptional standards in research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as managing the office’s workload, you’ll manage filing systems and diaries, handle queries and facilitate communication between the office and other departments. You’ll also provide training and support to other team members. Negotiation is everything in this role, as you’ll need to build effective relationships, resolve issues and manage stakeholders from across the organisation and externally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have administrative experience in complex, multi-disciplinary environments, organising workloads, dealing with stakeholders, and resolving issues. You’ll also be exceptionally well organised with excellent customer service skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also need candidates who can take dictation, produce clear, concise reports and effectively chase progress on agreed actions. Strong IT skills are essential (especially MS Outlook), and you should have a degree or equivalent in a relevant subject.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is so much to be said about the job satisfaction that our team members get from their work. With us, you’ll be at the heart of an organisation that’s saving and transforming countless lives every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At NHSBT, we also value the immense knowledge that our highly skilled team brings to our work. We’ll invest heavily in your personal and professional needs, from progressive training and development opportunities through to competitive pension schemes and generous annual leave allowance. It’s about making sure every NHSBT employee is truly happy in their work. Join us, experience a great work-life balance and a sense of achievement that can’t be found anywhere else.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time, permanent position working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This advert will close at 23:59 on Wednesday 11th November. (Subject to change)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact the R &amp; D Office via email at: research.office@nhsbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The interviews for this position are anticipated to take place on week commencing 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an inclusive organisation that reflects the diverse communities we work with and positively encourage applications from all sectors of the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Three small words, one big difference - Caring, Expert and Quality.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Together we&#39;ll save and improve more lives than ever.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
